# SurveyTool

If you intend to display a stacked page message after page load, for screen readers to announce the change, make sure the page message is rendered in a page region with `aria-live=“assertive”` or `role="alert"`.
Once a page message in stacked page message is closed, the focus should move to the next page message or next focusable element on the page.

Page messages within the Stacked Page Message will be sitting inside a landmark:

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/survey-tool
```

```tsx
import { SurveyTool } from '@ids-ts/survey-tool';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `question` | `string` | Yes | * Question posed to user, use appropriate heading level for document hierarchy |
| `analyticsKey` | `string` | Yes | * Unique key of implementation, used to differentiate one location in product from another |
| `analyticsVersion` | `string` | No | - |
| `sandbox` | `Sandbox` | Yes | * QBO sandbox, used for analytics tracking |
| `onSubmit` | `(response: ResponseKey) => void` | No | * Callback function executed when survey is completed by user |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | * Test automation ID |
| `scopeArea` | `string` | No | * enumScopeArea from analytics-lib package |
| `className` | `string` | No | * additional css classes to add to the component |
| `submittedMessage` | `string` | No | * Message shown after submitting |
| `onVerbatimSubmit` | `() => void` | No | * Callback function that gets executed when user submits their verbatim feedback |
| `onSurveyComplete` | `() => void` | No | * Callback function that gets executed when all inputs completed |
| `verbatimButton` | `string` | No | - |
| `collectVerbatimFor` | `{ [key in ResponseKey]?: string }` | No | - |
| `positiveAriaLabel` | `string` | No | * The aria label to apply to the positive happy smiley face |
| `neutralAriaLabel` | `string` | No | * The aria label to apply to the neutral face |
| `negativeAriaLabel` | `string` | No | * The aria label to apply to the negative frowny face |
| `analytics` | `Analytics` | Yes | * Interface for QBO sandbox object |
| `trackLogicalEvent` | `(event: Record<string, unknown>) => void` | Yes | * Analytics field on QBO sandbox. Use field trackLogicalEvent which is a function to dispatch tracking object to vertica |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface SurveyToolProps
  extends Omit<ThemeableElement<'div'>, 'onSubmit'> {
  /**
   * Question posed to user, use appropriate heading level for document hierarchy
   */
  question: string;
  /**
   * Unique key of implementation, used to differentiate one location in product from another
   */
  analyticsKey: string;
  /**
   * Optional, use to subdivide campaigns. E.g. analyticsKey="UKTaxFiling", analyticsVersion might be "refile1"
   * if users can re-file and you want to subdivide up the tracking for first time and repeat.
   * Appended to ObjectDetail in tracking with a | to separate e.g. "UKTaxFiling|refile1".
   */
  analyticsVersion?: string;
  /**
   * QBO sandbox, used for analytics tracking
   */
  sandbox: Sandbox;
  /**
   * Callback function executed when survey is completed by user
   */
  onSubmit?: (response: ResponseKey) => void;
  /**
   * Test automation ID
   */
  automationId?: string;
  /**
   * enumScopeArea from analytics-lib package
   */
  scopeArea?: string;
  /**
   * additional css classes to add to the component
   */
  className?: string;
  /**
   * Message shown after submitting
   */
  submittedMessage?: string;
  /**
   * Callback function that gets executed when user submits their verbatim feedback
   */
  onVerbatimSubmit?: () => void;
  /**
   * Callback function that gets executed when all inputs completed
   */
  onSurveyComplete?: () => void;
  /**
   * Text user uses to submit their verbatim feedback, typically "Send" or an appropriate translation
   * Required for the verbatim survey step to show
   */
  verbatimButton?: string;
  /**
   * Map of response key to verbatim questions
   * If a verbatim question is provided for a response type along with a value for the button,
   * the user is asked an additional question
   */
  collectVerbatimFor?: { [key in ResponseKey]?: string };

  /**
   * The aria label to apply to the positive happy smiley face
   */
  positiveAriaLabel?: string;
  /**
   * The aria label to apply to the neutral face
   */
  neutralAriaLabel?: string;
  /**
   * The aria label to apply to the negative frowny face
   */
  negativeAriaLabel?: string;
}

export interface Sandbox {
  /**
   * Interface for QBO sandbox object
   */
  analytics: Analytics;
}

interface Analytics {
  /**
   * Analytics field on QBO sandbox. Use field trackLogicalEvent which is a function to dispatch tracking object to vertica
   */
  trackLogicalEvent: (event: Record<string, unknown>) => void;
}

export enum ResponseKey {
  'positive' = 1,
  'neutral' = 0,
  'negative' = -1
}
```

</details>

